    "language": "english",
    "persons": [],
    "text": "BEIJING (Reuters) - China’s central bank issued new guidelines for the bond market that seek to limit leverage ratios and ban transactions designed to circumvent regulations.\nIn a joint statement signed by the People’s Bank of China and other financial security regulators, the central bank said bond market participants must strictly abide by liquidity and leverage ratio requirements.\nReporting by Beijing Monitoring Desk; Editing by Nick Macfie\n ",
